C1491- remove access notes for lowest-level components in Writings series

comments.body: @faithc Can you post the result of your query of the EAD here please? (The one with the access notes you want removed.)

Preliminary analysis:
ao aspace_C1491_c1 is 
- linked to 1447 ao's
- linked to 1340 ao's lacking links to ao's
- linked to 882 ao's with restriction notes (and has one itself)
- linked to 868 ao's lacking links to ao's and with restriction notes
- linked to 867 ao's lacking links to ao's and with restrictions

> @faithc Can you post the result of your query of the EAD here please? (The one with the access notes you want removed.)

Query is probably too generous a word. Ha I basically just did a search for accessrestrict tags for the subseries within the first series (I deleted the remaining series in the EAD). And actually, it looks like there are 880 notes with type “restricted,” not 883. It looks like I can't attach xml files here. Should I email you the revised EAD file I used to do the search? Would that be helpful at all? I don't know how to write an xquery to extract certain elements to save as a spreadsheet.

Hmmm. None of my queries (see above) get to 880. Let me ask you a few questions so I know what to query for:
- components at the lowest level means ao's that are not aggregates, i.e. terminal components in the XML serialization?
- are you looking to delete just the note? If so, I don't think that's possible in the current version without deleting the entire restriction. Does that change things?
- are you looking to delete only restrictions of a certain type?

Here is an XPath that will get you any leaf components within Series 1 that have an accessrestrict, which is what I'm understanding you're trying to get at--perhaps review that and let me know how it doesn't match your search criteria (since the number of results doesn't match yours)? I'm skeptical that it's really what you need, but it's a place to start.

`//c[@id="aspace_C1491_c1"]//c[not(c)]/accessrestrict`

princeton_ansible.title: Mysql Users No Longer have permission to run sql-dump

comments.body: * putting deploy in the sudoers file so that it can do mysqldump as root

Discussed a few possible solutions:
* creating a playbook for one-time database dumps (probably run as mysql and not through drush)
* putting deploy in the sudoers file so that it can do mysqldump as root
* creating a capistrano task to do the dumps ([example](https://github.com/pulibrary/pul_library_drupal/blob/main/config/deploy.rb#L203-L210))
We confirmed that the backups are not affected at today's Ansible Open House.
Here is an example of adding a specific task to the [sudoers](https://github.com/pulibrary/pul_library_drupal/blob/main/config/deploy.rb#L203-L210)

comments.body:
Check out the commit https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/commit/cdeeaed86a4c38028961a37f26d237c5b7d0cb13 For network pre task.  It was removed (but we may still need it for other reasons in other roles)

```
 pre_tasks:
    - name: install iproute
      apt:
        name: iproute2
        state: present
        update_cache: true
    - name: rerun setup
      setup:
        gather_subset:
          - network
 ```

☝️ The information above is helpful, but does not solve this problem because the network is not configured.  The machine will have a network configuration and IP address.  We will create a PR to remove the bind9 start from molecule.

tiger-data-app.title: Confirm access and privileges on TigerData staging server

comments.body:
All the `sudo -l` commands listed that point to `/home/MFLUX/volatile/...` worked for me and I suspect that's all we really need.

The few `sudo -l` commands that pointed to `/var/log/messages` and `/var/log/secure` ~~DID NOT work for me~~. Correction, they do work for me. Looking at my shell history I noticed that I had ran then without `sudo` 🤦🏼

`sudo /usr/bin/cat /var/log/messages` and `sudo /usr/bin/cat /var/log/secure` worked for me.
So did everything else I tried.

These all work for me:
```
    sudo tail /var/log/messages
    sudo tail /var/log/secure
    sudo tail /home/MFLUX/volatile/logs/http.2.log
    sudo tail /home/MFLUX/volatile/logs/mediaflux-server.log
    sudo tail /home/MFLUX/volatile/logs/internal.1.log
    sudo tail /home/MFLUX/volatile/logs/syslog.log
```
